snippet.title: The Conjuring: Last Rites | Official Teaser
snippet.description:
Last Case. Last Rites. #TheConjuring: Last Rites - Only in Theaters September 5.

From New Line Cinema comes the ninth entry in the more than $2 billion theatrical Conjuring universe, The Conjuring: Last Rites, directed by franchise veteran Michael Chaves and produced by franchise architects James Wan and Peter Safran.

The Conjuring: Last Rites delivers another thrilling chapter of the iconic Conjuring cinematic universe, based on real events. Vera Farmiga and Patrick Wilson reunite for one last case as renowned, real-life paranormal investigators Ed and Lorraine Warren in a powerful and spine-chilling addition to the global box office-breaking franchise.

Farmiga and Wilson star alongside Mia Tomlinson and Ben Hardy, who portray Ed and Lorraine‚Äôs daughter Judy Warren and her boyfriend, Tony Spera, as well as Steve Coulter returning as Father Gordon, Rebecca Calder, Elliot Cowan, K√≠la Lord Cassidy, Beau Gadsdon, John Brotherton and Shannon Kook.

Chaves directs from a screenplay by Ian Goldberg & Richard Naing and David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, story by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick & James Wan, based on characters created by Chad Hayes & Carey W. Hayes. 

The executive producers are Michael Clear, Judson Scott, Natalia Safran, John Rickard, Hans Ritter and David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick. Chaves is joined behind the camera by his creative team, including director of photography Eli Born, production designer John Frankish, editors Elliot Greenberg and Gregory Plotkin, visual effects supervisor Scott Edelstein, visual effects producer Eric Bruneau and costume designer Graham Churchyard, with casting by Rose Wicksteed and Sophie Kingston-Smith. 

The music supervisor is Ian Broucek and the music is by composer Benjamin Wallfisch. New Line Cinema Presents A Safran Company / An Atomic Monster Production, The Conjuring: Last Rites. The film will be released worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures and will be only in theaters and IMAX¬Æ in North America on September 5, 2025, and internationally beginning 3 September 2025.

snippet.title: Mafia: The Old Country - Official Gameplay Trailer
snippet.description:
Here's your look at gameplay in this new Mafia: The Old Country trailer for the upcoming third-person action-adventure game. Uncover the origins of organized crime in Mafia: The Old Country, a gritty mob story set in the brutal underworld of 1900s Sicily. Mafia: The Old Country will be available on PS5 (PlayStation 5), Xbox Series X/S, and PC (Steam) on August 8, 2025.

Here's your look at gameplay in this new Mafia: The Old Country trailer for the upcoming third-person action-adventure game. Uncover the origins of organized crime in Mafia: The Old Country, a gritty mob story set in the brutal underworld of 1900s Sicily. Mafia: The Old Country will be available on PS5 (PlayStation 5), Xbox Series X/S, and PC (Steam) on August 8, 2025.

snippet.title: Pakistan's UK high commissioner warns country will strike back at India
snippet.description:
Pakistan's high commissioner to the UK has told Yalda Hakim his country wants peace - but there is "no doubt" Islamabad will respond to India's attack.

Mohammad Faisal said "Pakistan's first choice was peace" and the country would cooperate with an international investigation into the attack on Indian civilians in Indian-administered Kashmir last week.

However, he warned: "They are throwing missiles at our country, how are we supposed to collaborate with them?"

P1Harmony, a group that continues to break own records with every release, is back with 8th Mini Album ‚ÄúDUH!‚Äù on May 8th. 

In previous album, P1Harmony explored the loneliness and emptiness felt by a HERO, shedding light on the hidden struggles behind heroism and unveiling yet another side of the HERO. The 8th Mini Album, 'DUH!' introduces a HERO who refuses to be taken for granted, boldly asking, ‚ÄúYou really don‚Äôt need us?‚Äù and going on strike in response. It flips the idea that heroes must always be noble, instead portraying a bold, free-spirited side of P1Harmony with a playful twist.

The title track 'DUH!', which shares its name with the album, embodies the album's core message. Built on a vintage beat with a retro-inspired groove, the song merges old-school charm with P1Harmony‚Äôs trendsetting vocal style. The title track 'DUH!' is an expression conveying the attitude of "Who‚Äôs the big shot here? Of course, it‚Äôs me! Isn‚Äôt that obvious?" and playfully showcases a more self-assured and bold version of the HERO. Unlike the traditional HERO, who is righteous and humble, this HERO asserts an undeniable presence with lines like "Where I sit, and the path I walk is the answer."

The performance emphasizes freestyle dance, bringing fresh and hip vibes compared to previous routines. The key move of 'DUH!' was created by INTAK, while SOUL contributed to the choreography in the final chorus, further highlighting P1Harmony‚Äôs distinctive style. One of the performance‚Äôs highlights of 'DUH!' is how each member interprets the same movements in own unique way, making a dynamic and individualistic freestyle expression.

Built on a vintage beat with a retro-inspired groove, the song merges old-school charm with P1Harmony‚Äôs trendsetting vocal style. The title track 'DUH!' is an expression conveying the attitude of "Who‚Äôs the big shot here? Of course, it‚Äôs me! Isn‚Äôt that obvious?" and playfully showcases a more self-assured and bold version of the HERO. Unlike the traditional HERO, who is righteous and humble, this HERO asserts an undeniable presence with lines like "Where I sit, and the path I walk is the answer."

The performance emphasizes freestyle dance, bringing fresh and hip vibes compared to previous routines. The key move of 'DUH!' was created by INTAK, while SOUL contributed to the choreography in the final chorus, further highlighting P1Harmony‚Äôs distinctive style. One of the performance‚Äôs highlights of 'DUH!' is how each member interprets the same movements in own unique way, making a dynamic and individualistic freestyle expression.
